# Component Standards

## Folder Structure

Every component is a directory inside `src/components/` (flat, no category nesting):

```
ComponentName/
├── index.ts              # Barrel export
├── ComponentName.tsx      # Presentation (JSX only, no business logic)
├── ComponentName.types.ts # Props interface, local types, local enums
├── useComponentName.ts    # Logic hook (state, effects, handlers) — only if needed
├── ComponentName.styles.css # Scoped CSS — only if Tailwind can't handle it
└── SubComponent.tsx       # Sub-components stay in parent folder
```

## Small, Focused, Reusable

- **Max 600 lines per file.** Aim for 50–150 lines.
- One component per file. File name = component name in PascalCase.
- If you can describe a component with "and," split it.

## Presentation vs. Logic Split

Components with state, effects, or handlers MUST split into:
- `ComponentName.tsx` — pure presentation. Same props → same output.
- `useComponentName.ts` — logic hook returning a typed object.

Skip the hook only for purely presentational components (Badge, Heading, Icon).

## Props — Strict Typing

- **`any` is banned.** Use `unknown` + narrowing if needed.
- Props interface named `ComponentNameProps` in `ComponentName.types.ts`.
- Extend native HTML props: `React.ComponentPropsWithoutRef<"button">`.
- Use discriminated unions for variant-based components.
- Every primitive accepts `className` for one-off overrides.

```ts
// Button.types.ts
export enum ButtonVariant { PRIMARY = "primary", SECONDARY = "secondary", GHOST = "ghost" }
export enum ButtonSize { SM = "sm", MD = "md", LG = "lg" }

export interface ButtonProps extends React.ComponentPropsWithoutRef<"button"> {
  variant?: ButtonVariant;
  size?: ButtonSize;
  children: React.ReactNode;
  isLoading?: boolean;
}
```

## Barrel Exports

Every component folder has `index.ts`:

```ts
export { Button } from "./Button";
export type { ButtonProps } from "./Button.types";
```

## General Patterns

- Functional components only. Class components allowed ONLY for error boundaries.
- Named exports for all components. Default exports only if required by TanStack Router.
- Prefer composition over configuration — pass children, not dozens of config props.
- All user-facing text via `useTranslation` — zero hardcoded strings.
